    Gettysburg Address   
   Main Gettysburg Address  
 Although the   Battle of Gettysburg   was a Union victory  it was also the bloodiest battle of the war and dealt a blow to Lincoln's war effort  As the Union Army decreased in numbers due to casualties  more soldiers were needed to replace the ranks  Lincoln's      military drafts were considered  quot odious quot  among many in the north  particularly immigrants  The   New York Draft Riots   of July      were the most notable manifestation of this discontent 
 Writing to Lincoln in September       the   List of Governors of Pennsylvania Governor of Pennsylvania      Andrew Gregg Curtin    warned that political sentiments were turning against Lincoln and the war effort 
  lt blockquote gt ''If the election were to occur now  the result would be extremely doubtful  and although most of our discreet friends are sanguine of the result  my impression is  the chances would be against us  The draft is very odious in the State    the Democratic leaders have succeeded in exciting prejudice and passion  and have infused their poison into the minds of the people to a very large extent  and the changes are against us '' lt ref gt   cite web  accessdate             url http   memory loc gov cgi bin query r ammem mal  field DOCID  lit d          title Andrew G  Curtin to Abraham Lincoln  Friday  September          Politics in Pennsylvania  publisher   Library of Congress    date             author Curtin  Andrew G    lt  ref gt  lt  blockquote gt 
 The ''Gettysburg Address'' is one of the most quoted speeches in   History of the United States United States history    lt ref gt   cite web url http   usinfo state gov usa infousa facts democrac    htm  archiveurl http   web archive org web                http   usinfo state gov usa infousa facts democrac    htm  archivedate             title Introduction to Abraham Lincoln's Gettysburg Address  publisher United States Department of State  work InfoUSA  accessdate             quote Few documents in the growth of American democracy are as well known or as beloved as the prose poem Abraham Lincoln delivered at the dedication of the military cemetery in Gettysburg  Pennsylvania    lt  ref gt  lt ref gt   cite web url http   www bartleby com    ge GettysbuAd html  title Gettysburg Address  accessdate             work Columbia Encyclopedia   th Edition  month May  year       publisher Columbia University Press via   Bartleby com    quote It is one of the most famous and most quoted of modern speeches    lt  ref gt  lt ref gt Historian   James M  McPherson James McPherson   has called it  quot The most eloquent expression of the new birth of freedom brought forth by reform liberalism  quot   in McPherson  James M  ''Drawn with the Sword  Reflections on the American Civil War'' Oxford  Oxford University Press        p       Google Book Search  Retrieved on November           lt  ref gt  It was delivered at the dedication of the   Gettysburg National Cemetery Soldiers' National Cemetery   in   Gettysburg  Pennsylvania    on the afternoon of Thursday  November           during the   American Civil War    four and a half months after the   Union  American Civil War  Union   armies defeated those of the   Confederate States of America Confederacy   at the decisive   Battle of Gettysburg   
 Abraham Lincoln's carefully crafted address  secondary to other presentations that day  came to be regarded as one of the greatest speeches in American history  In just over two minutes  Lincoln invoked the principles of human equality espoused by the   United States Declaration of Independence Declaration of Independence   and redefined the Civil War as a struggle not merely for the   United States Union    but as  quot a new birth of   political freedom freedom   quot  that would bring true equality to all of its citizens  and that would also create a unified nation in which   states' rights   were no longer dominant 
 Beginning with the now iconic phrase  ''Four       number  score   and seven years ago   ''  Lincoln referred to the events of the   American Civil War Civil War   and described the ceremony at Gettysburg as an opportunity not only to consecrate the grounds of a cemetery  but also to dedicate the living to the struggle to ensure that  quot government of the people  by the people  for the people  shall not perish from the earth quot   lt ref gt  Garry Willis  ''Lincoln at Gettysburg  The Words That Remade America''        lt  ref gt 
         election and second inauguration   
   File Republican presidential ticket     b jpg thumb left   Currier and Ives   print of the   National Union Party  United States  National Union Party   presidential candidates        Lithograph and watercolor   
   Main United States presidential election        
 After Union victories at   Battle of Gettysburg Gettysburg      Siege of Vicksburg Vicksburg    and   Chattanooga Campaign Chattanooga   in       overall victory seemed at hand  and Lincoln promoted   Ulysses S  Grant   General in Chief on March           When the spring campaigns turned into bloody stalemates  Lincoln supported Grant's strategy of wearing down   Robert E  Lee Lee's   Confederate army at the cost of heavy Union casualties  With an election looming  he easily defeated efforts to deny his renomination  At the Convention  the Republican Party selected   Andrew Johnson    a   War Democrats War Democrat   from the Southern state of Tennessee  as his running mate in order to form a broader coalition  They ran on the new   National Union Party  United States  Union Party   ticket uniting Republicans and War Democrats 
   File ElectoralCollege     svg    px      Presidential election results thumb  
 Nevertheless  Republicans across the country feared that Lincoln would be defeated  Acknowledging this fear  Lincoln wrote and signed a pledge that  if he should lose the election  he would still defeat the Confederacy before turning over the White House  lt ref gt 
   cite book
