 Lincoln's death made the President a national   martyr    lt ref gt   cite book last Naveh first Eyal J   title Crown of Thorns  Political Martyrdom in America From Abraham Lincoln to Martin Luther King  Jr  publisher NYU Press date      pages    isbn                 lt  ref gt  Repeated polls of historians have ranked Lincoln as among the   Historical rankings of United States Presidents greatest presidents in U S  history    with Lincoln usually in the top three along with George Washington and Franklin D  Roosevelt  lt ref gt   cite book last Bose first Meenekshi  coauthors Mark Landis title The uses and abuses of presidential ratings publisher Nova Publishers date      pages   isbn                 lt  ref gt   A study published in       found that scholars in the fields of history and politics ranked Lincoln number one  while law scholars placed him second after Washington  lt ref gt   cite book last Taranto first James  coauthors Leonard Leo title Presidential leadership  rating the best and the worst in the White House publisher Simon and Schuster pages     isbn                 lt  ref gt   Among contemporary admirers  Lincoln is usually seen as personifying classical values of honesty and integrity  as well as respect for individual and minority rights  and human freedom in general 
 Many American organizations of all purposes and agendas continue to cite his name and image  with interests ranging from the   LGBT rights in the United States gay rights   supporting   Log Cabin Republicans   to the   insurance   corporation   Lincoln National Corporation    The   Lincoln  automobile  Lincoln automobile brand   is also named after him 
 The   ballistic missile     submarine     USS Abraham Lincoln  SSBN      ''Abraham Lincoln''  SSBN        and the   aircraft carrier     USS Abraham Lincoln  CVN     ''Abraham Lincoln''  CVN       were named in his honor  lt ref gt   cite book last Sweetman first Jack  title American Naval History  An Illustrated Chronology of the U S  Navy and Marine Corps       Present publisher Naval Institute Press date      pages               isbn                 lt  ref gt  During the   Spanish Civil War    the American faction of the   International Brigades   named themselves the   Abraham Lincoln Brigade    lt ref gt   cite book last Carroll first Peter N   title The odyssey of the Abraham Lincoln Brigade  Americans in the Spanish Civil War publisher Stanford University Press date      isbn                 lt  ref gt   Lincoln has been memorialized in many town  city  and county names  lt ref name  quot Dennis quot  gt   cite book last Dennis first Matthew  title Red  white  and blue letter days  an American calendar publisher Cornell University Press date      pages     isbn                 lt  ref gt  including the   Lincoln  Nebraska capital of Nebraska    lt ref name  quot Boritt quot  gt   cite book last Boritt first G  S   title The Gettysburg gospel  the Lincoln speech that nobody knows publisher Simon and Schuster date      pages     isbn                 lt  ref gt       Lincoln  Illinois    is the only city to be named for Abraham Lincoln before he became President  lt ref gt   cite book last Reinhart first Mark S   title Abraham Lincoln on Screen  Fictional and Documentary Portrayals on Film and Television publisher McFarland date      pages    isbn                 lt  ref gt 
 Lincoln's name and image appear in numerous places  These include the   Lincoln Memorial   in Washington  D C   lt ref name  quot Boritt quot   gt  the U S    United States five dollar bill Lincoln    bill   and the   Lincoln cent     Lincoln's sculpture on   Mount Rushmore    and the   Lincoln Home National Historic Site   in Springfield  Illinois  lt ref gt   cite book last Peterson first Merrill D   title Lincoln in American Memory publisher Oxford University Press US date      pages          isbn                 lt  ref gt  In addition    New Salem  Menard County  Illinois New Salem  Illinois    a reconstruction of Lincoln's early adult hometown   lt ref gt   cite web url http   www lincolnsnewsalem com  title Lincoln's New Salem State Historic Site accessdate              lt  ref gt     Ford's Theatre    and Petersen House  where he died  are all preserved as museums  lt ref gt   cite web url http   www fordstheatre org home about fords title About Ford's accessdate              lt  ref gt   The   List of U S  state nicknames state nickname   for Illinois is ''Land of Lincoln''  the slogan has appeared continuously on nearly all   Vehicle registration plates of Illinois Illinois license plates   issued since       lt ref gt   cite web url http   www cyberdriveillinois com special plate history           pdf title      amp ndash     plate history publisher Ilinois DMV accessdate              lt  ref gt 
 Abraham Lincoln's birthday  February     was never a national holiday  but it was observed by    states  lt ref name  quot Dennis quot   gt   In        Presidents Day  United States  Presidents Day   became a national holiday  combining Lincoln's and Washington's birthdays  and replacing most state's celebration of his birthday  lt ref gt   cite book last Schwartz first Barry  title Abraham Lincoln in the Post Heroic Era  History and Memory in Late Twentieth Century America publisher University of Chicago Press date      pages     amp ndash     isbn                 lt  ref gt   However  it is still observed in Illinois and many other states as a separate legal holiday    Lincoln's Birthday    A dozen states have legal holidays celebrating the third Monday in February as Presidents Day as a combination Washington Lincoln Day   The   Abraham Lincoln Association   was formed in      to commemorate the centennial of Lincoln's birth   The Association is now the oldest group dedicated to the study of Lincoln 
 To commemorate his upcoming    th birthday in February       Congress established the   Abraham Lincoln Bicentennial Commission    ALBC  in       Dedicated to renewing American appreciation of Lincoln's legacy  the    member commission is made up of lawmakers and scholars and also features an advisory board of over     various Lincoln historians and enthusiasts  Located at   Library of Congress   in   Washington  D C     the ALBC is the organizing force behind numerous tributes  programs and cultural events highlighting a two year celebration scheduled to begin in February      at Lincoln's birthplace    Hodgenville  Kentucky Hodgenville      Kentucky   
 Lincoln's birthplace and family home are national historic memorials  the   Abraham Lincoln Birthplace National Historic Site   in Hodgenville  and the Lincoln Home National Historic Site in Springfield  Illinois  The   Abraham Lincoln Presidential Library and Museum   opened in Springfield in       it is a major tourist attraction  with state of the art exhibits  The   Abraham Lincoln National Cemetery   is located in   Elwood  Illinois    The  http   www lmunet edu museum Index html Abraham Lincoln Library and Museum  is located in   Harrogate  Tennessee   
 On Wednesday    March      the   National Museum of American History   found a message engraved inside Lincoln's watch by a watchmaker named Jonathan Dillon who was repairing it at the outbreak of the   American Civil War    The engraving reads  in part    quot   Fort Sumpter   was attacked by the rebels quot  and  quot thank God we have a government  quot 
